Kernel Version: 4.10.0-rc6+

2. The steps I followed while compiling the latest kernel are as follows:

 Firstly I installed Virtual box from internet.

 Then I loaded Ubuntu 16.04 iso image into that virtual box to install Ubuntu

operating system into it.

 Then, I ran these following commands:

 sudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev gcc make git

exuberant-ctags bc libssl-dev

 git clone

git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux-

stable.git

 cd linux-stable

 git clone

git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linu

x.git

 cd linux

 cp /boot/config-`uname -r`* .config

 make defconfig

 make

 make -j4

 sudo make modules_install install

 sudo update-grub2

 reboot

 Then my virtual system restarts.

 While restarting, I kept shift button pressed.

 And finally I got to the grub menu which shows me all the options through

which I can log into my system.

 I chose 4.10.0-rc6+ to log into the my kernel.
